        <h2>Computer Organization and Architecture</h2>
        <div class="questions">
          <div class="question">
            <p>What is computer organization and architecture?</p>
            <div class="answer">Computer organization and architecture is the study of the physical components and internal workings of computer systems, including the design of processors, memory systems, and input/output devices.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="question">
            <p>What is the difference between RISC and CISC processors?</p>
            <div class="answer">RISC (Reduced Instruction Set Computing) and CISC (Complex Instruction Set Computing) are two different approaches to processor design. RISC processors have a simpler instruction set, with each instruction performing a basic operation. CISC processors, on the other hand, have a more complex instruction set, with each instruction capable of performing multiple operations. In general, RISC processors are faster and more power-efficient, while CISC processors are more flexible and can handle more complex tasks.</div>
          </div>
         <div class="subject">
        <h2>Machine Learning</h2>
        <div class="questions">
          <div class="question">
            <p>What is deep learning?</p>
            <div class="answer">Deep learning is a type of machine learning that uses neural networks with multiple layers to learn hierarchical representations of data.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="question">
            <p>What is transfer learning in machine learning?</p>
            <div class="answer">Transfer learning is a technique in machine learning where a model trained on one task is re-purposed for a different but related task, often with fewer training examples required.</div>
            </div>
             <div class="subject">
        <h2>Analysis and design of algorithm</h2>
        <div class="questions">
          <div class="question">
            <p>What is dynamic programming?</p>
            <div class="answer">Dynamic programming is a technique for solving optimization problems by breaking them down into smaller subproblems and storing the solutions to these subproblems to avoid redundant calculations.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="question">
            <p>What is the difference between Greedy and Dynamic programming algorithms?</p>
            <div class="answer">Greedy algorithms make locally optimal choices at each step to find a globally optimal solution, whereas dynamic programming algorithms solve problems by breaking them down into smaller subproblems and storing the solutions to these subproblems to avoid redundant calculations.
          </div>
        </div>
